{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a27a352-1d0d-4ab7-9d42-bbb35d36fa6b","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX + coverage:\n\n### 1. Update your test `.csproj`\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: Run tests\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: Publish test results\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: Publish code coverage\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** makes MSTest use Microsoft.Testing.Platform as its host.\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** keeps `dotnet test` working (otherwise you'd need to run the test exe directly).\n- **`--logger trx`** produces the same TRX files VSTest did.\n- **`--collect \"Code Coverage\"`** uses the Microsoft code-coverage collector; for Cobertura XML output add the `Format=Cobertura` setting or use `coverlet`.\n- **`PublishTestResults@2`** and **`PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`** replace the built-in reporting that `VSTest@3` did automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"559156f5-8f98-4693-8cfd-a024d0c0e9c6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory appears to be empty and doesn't contain relevant repository content. Let me provide a direct answer based on my knowledge of migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines.","outputTokens":651,"requestId":"0BD7:1BE4D:2268DE:281EB6:69F0050C"},"id":"43340ab5-0c90-4735-87e5-e0003205985c","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:53:44.873Z","parentId":"de012c56-69ce-40a0-a590-1bfeb34b1f82"}
